<subSubSection id="C31E6567FFE0F60E89B637C6FCB3FBEA" pageId="36" pageNumber="94" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="8BBB36ECFFE0F60E89B637C6FCB3FBEA" blockId="36.[165,1374,276,1220]" pageId="36" pageNumber="94">
<emphasis id="B970EAFEFFE0F60E89B637C6FDA4FC60" bold="true" box="[168,513,986,1019]" pageId="36" pageNumber="94">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Least Concern on The IUCNRed List. Despite loss of lowland forests, there is too little evidence to assign Bergman's Collared Fruit Bat to a higher conservation category. 
<taxonomicName id="4C044D6FFFE0F60E8B6E3035FD66FBD1" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1910" box="[624,707,1065,1098]" class="Mammalia" family="Pteropodidae" genus="Eonycteris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="36" pageNumber="94" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="major">Major</taxonomicName>
threats include logging of forests for firewood and conversion of forests to agricultural use.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
